basics.name: Eugene Yamenko
basics.label: Senior Software Engineer
basics.summary:
Senior Software Engineer with many years of experience in the software development field.
● Skillful in backend, frontend and cloud technologies (.NET, React, AWS).
● Possession of strong communication and mentoring skills.
● Experience designing and building complex large scale data driven systems.
● Knowledge of best practices across the full software development life cycle.

work.summary: Domain Group offers an ecosystem of leading multi-platform property solutions.
highlights: Converted legacy listing processing systems to use APIs.
Built a client application for support to manage listings in migration between CRM providers.
Integrated with an external partner to display agents’ reviews.
Re-factored, stabilized and optimized numerous listing processing and listing retrieval components.
Built a client application for agents to manage related development projects.
Was nominated for an internal recognition program for being passionate about software development practices.

work.summary: InfoTrack is the leading innovator in legal technology.
highlights: Split company’s main monolithic application into a smaller maintainable applications.
Built an email service, used by all other teams.
Participated in the architectural group, which advised on software design and architecture.

work.summary: ClickView is Australia’s leading educational video company.
highlights: Built a system to send out and track promotional and recommendation emails.
Built a client application for end users to store and manage uploaded videos.
Implemented a custom integration with Salesforce.
Built an application for curators to manage video resources.
Organized and regularly presented at monthly internal meetups.
